  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 37 of 1972, s. 2 (w.e.f. 20-8-1972).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00001_197028_1517807317180&sectionId=43697&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00001_197028_1517807317180
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Supreme Court (Enlargement of Criminal`
  line `Appellate Jurisdiction) Act, 1970.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1`
  line ***.
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (43698)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Enlarged appellate jurisdiction of Supreme Court in regard to criminal matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00001_197028_1517807317180&sectionId=43698&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00001_197028_1517807317180
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line Without
  line `prejudice to the powers conferred on the Supreme Court by clause (1) of article 134 of the Constitution,`
  line `an appeal shall lie to the Supreme Court from any judgment, final order or sentence in a criminal`
  line `proceeding of a High Court in the territory of India if the High Court—`
  line
  line `(a) has on appeal reversed an order of acquittal of an accused person and sentenced him to`
  line `imprisonment for life or to imprisonment for a period of not less than ten years;`
  line
  line `(b) has withdrawn for trial before itself any case from any court subordinate to its authority and`
  line `has in such trial convicted the accused person and sentenced him to imprisonment for life or to`
  line `imprisonment for a period of not less than ten years.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
